=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: From methyl 7-bromo-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidine-5-carboxylate, install cyclopropyl by Pd-catalyzed coupling with cyclopropylboronic acid (or cyclopropyltrifluoroborate), Pd(dppf)Cl2, K2CO3, dioxane/H2O, to give methyl 7-cyclopropyl-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidine-5-carboxylate | Step 2: Hydrolyze the methyl ester (LiOH or NaOH, THF/H2O/MeOH) to 7-cyclopropyl-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidine-5-carboxylic acid | Step 3: In parallel, protect methyl 3-aminobutanoate with Boc2O/base to give methyl 3-(tert-butoxycarbonylamino)butanoate | Step 4: Convert that ester to the N-ethyl amide by aminolysis with ethylamine to form 3-(tert-butoxycarbonylamino)-N-ethylbutanamide | Step 5: Remove Boc with TFA/CH2Cl2 to give 3-amino-N-ethylbutanamide | Step 6: Couple 7-cyclopropyl-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidine-5-carboxylic acid with 3-amino-N-ethylbutanamide using HATU/DIPEA (or EDCI/HOBt, PyBOP) in DMF to furnish the target CCNC(=O)CC(C)NC(=O)c1c[nH]c2ncc(C3CC3)nc12.

